This is a reference card of useful commands for administrating gentoo. # denotes comments of what the command does.

=Portage Package Management=
{{RootCmd|emerge --sync #old method download latest package information from the mirror.}}
{{RootCmd|emerge-webrsync #new method download latest package information from the mirror.}}
{{RootCmd|eix-sync #sync the overlay and run emerge --sync in one command.}}
{{RootCmd|emerge -pv cat/pkg #verbose simulation of package installation.}}
{{RootCmd|emerge {{=}}cat/pkg-1.0 #install special version of a package}}
{{RootCmd|emerge -cav cat/pkg #remove package with dependency checking}}
{{RootCmd|emerge -C cat/pkg #remove package without dependency checking, use with care}}
{{RootCmd|emerge -av --depclean #remove no longer needed packages}}
{{RootCmd|emerge -uDN world #upgrade the systems outdated packages, and use flag changes}}
{{Cmd|equery b "which vim" #tells which installed package provides pkg}}
{{Cmd|equery d cat/pkg #show packages that depend on cat/pkg}}
{{RootCmd|eix cat/pkg #documentation on a package}}
{{RootCmd|porthole #a gui for emerge}}
{{RootCmd|dispatch-conf #manage config changes after emerge}}
{{RootCmd|revdep-rebuild #rebuilds packages that depend on an recently updated library}}


==Use Flags==
{{Cmd|euse -i #returns a description on useflags}}
{{Cmd|euse -i | grep png #returns a description on the png useflag}}

==Typical Administration==
{{Cmd|sudo -s #used by a user from sudoers list to get a root shell}}
{{RootCmd|rc-update add sshd default #Start the ssh daemon in the default runlevel at boot}}
{{RootCmd|rc-service xdm start #Start the service now}}
{{RootCmd|rc-status sshd #check if sshd is running or not}}

